RELI 3351 - Major Religious Thinkers
This course introduces students to the thought, historical setting, and
influence of thinkers from Eastern and Western religious traditions. The
figures covered include traditional religious thinkers, such as the Biblical
prophets and Laozi; recent and contemporary religious thinkers, such as
Thomas Merton and the Dalai Lama; and critics of religion, such as Karl
Marx and Sigmund Freud.
